New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">as it is no longer viable? </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">It seems to me to be fairly well patronized, with many relying on these services as their transport home from work. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">I would be interested to see what figures they base this on and what the spread is over the day.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">This will now leaves</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">usurers with the last service leaving Taunton at 20.00hrs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">and Minehead, Bancks St at 07.45!! </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Instead of the now last services leaving 22.45 and 21.30 respectfully.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">We have already previously seen cuts to the evening buses on this route, with the withdrawal of funding from the Somerset County Council under their</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">austerity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">plans. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">This leaving a large gap, 20.00hrs - 22.45 with the Taunton departure. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">However, this at least keeps the ability to cover the day for people to get home. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">route and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">maintaining that coverage is essential to the community as without this flexibility it places great constrains on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">peoples ability to get to and from work, onward travel and homeward travel. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Stranded, because of a late train or plane, and so on.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">"First" have their buses poster out with "Our commitment to our customers. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">We believe that there should always be a bus when you need one"</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Really? </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">They do employ a great bunch of drivers, who as you can</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">imagine, are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">hardly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">impressed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">with that plaster over the inside of the bus!! </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">The state of the buses are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">disgraceful as they are well past their prime. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Four breakdowns last Friday and the doors jammed on the bus I was travelling on that day.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">I am sure that with a little imagination, a couple of the half hour services during the slack period of the day could be cut.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">There is also, during the day, the alternative"Webbers" 18 service, which, albeit a slightly different route, is transport to Taunton, giving 2 services an hour with "First" cutting one.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">I write this letter as a bus pass holder and also disabled and live on this route because of the service. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Nevertheless, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">it is NOT just self interest but written on behalf of a community that will suffer in many ways with a restricted bus service in this modern day and age.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">So, can you help your</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">constituents and bring some pressure to bear with at least maintaining our late night services?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">I look forward to your early replies.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Yours faithfully,</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Nick Mitcham.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">As I hope you will note, I have made some recommendations in the context of the letter, however, I list below some further thoughts below:-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">1. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">One of the saddest aspects of this, is the people who have had jobs that have depended on the late night service, who have had to quit as their employers are unable to shuffle hours to accommodate for the lack of a bus. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">(Information supplied by the Bus Drivers)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">2. First Buses lack a commitment to serve the Community, as of the reasons stated in my letter.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">3.Council funding should be reviewed within terms of contract or used differently to the best advantage of the community.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">4. Relating to the above. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">The introduction of a Bus Credit Pass (on the Web). </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">You have a Bus Pass Credit Account that you can credit and then use the pass for your journeys. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">There should be Residents passes (lower fares with the aid of council funding) offering different Radius miles from the address and priced accordingly.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Visitors Bus Passes on a 1day/3day/1week/2week etc.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">This will help 1. Funding for the buses. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">2. Ease of operation for drivers and passengers alike.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">5. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">I am sure there are many other ways that these services can be made more viable. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">I must say that cutting this last service on the 28 route to Minehead </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">on the 29th July, during the holiday season, is a sure fired way to lose revenue!! </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">On a final note, there is an X28 service that also operates direct (no visit to Watchet) that it would appear not everyone knows about. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">I followed one the other week....not a soul onboard!!! </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Enough said?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">I hope this proves of use in your deliberations and should require any further input I am able to offer, please feel free to contact me.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:14.5pt">Yours faithfully,</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-